{
  "to": [
    "[Your Name]"
  ],
  "subject": "Latest Admissions Cycle Highlights & Resources",
  "body": "Hi [Your Name],

Below is a concise overview of the most recent admissions cycle (incoming class of 2028) along with upcoming dates and resource links you can share with Sarah.

KEY INCOMING CLASS STATS
• Applicants: ~15,000 (↑5% year-over-year)
• Admitted students: 1,050 (selectivity 7%)
• Average SAT: 1480 | Average ACT: 33
• Geographic diversity: students hail from 60+ countries; roughly 28% hold non-U.S. passports
• Academic interests: most represented intended majors include Computer Science, Business, Biology, Economics, and Mechanical Engineering
• Standout profile themes: sustained community service leadership, entrepreneurship initiatives, and national-level research or arts achievements

UPCOMING ADMISSIONS-RELATED EVENTS & DATES FOR ALUMNI
• June 15 – Virtual “Ask an Admissions Dean” Q&A for alumni and new admits
• July 8–12 – Regional Send-Off receptions hosted by Alumni Chapters
• August 24 – Move-in & Convocation (official start of Welcome Week)
(The full calendar will be finalized by May 20; I’ll circulate the link once confirmed.)

ADDITIONAL RESOURCES
• Admissions Cycle Overview (Notion – internal): https://www.notion.so/Admissions-Cycle-2022-2023-Overview-2180dc8fa0db81dca2e2d038c8e043db
• Aggregate Class Highlights (Notion – internal): https://www.notion.so/Profiles-of-Admitted-Students-2180dc8fa0db81f29fb2ec1e2eae2e4e

Both pages contain aggregate data only; no personally identifiable applicant information is included. Let me know if you run into permission issues and I’ll grant access right away.

Please let me know if you need anything else or if Sarah has follow-up questions.

Best regards,
John",

---

Subject: Latest Admissions Cycle Highlights & Resources

Hi [Colleague’s Name],

Below is a concise overview of the most recent admissions cycle (incoming class of 2028) plus upcoming timelines and resource references you can pass along to Sarah.

KEY INCOMING CLASS STATS  
• Applicants: ≈ 15,000 (▲ 5% year-over-year)  
• Admitted students: 1,050 (selectivity ≈ 7%)  
• Average SAT: 1480  |  Average ACT: 33  
• Geographic diversity: students from 60+ countries; ~28 % hold non-U.S. passports  
• Academic interests: most represented intended majors – Computer Science, Business, Biology, Economics, Mechanical Engineering  
• Stand-out themes: sustained community-service leadership, entrepreneurship initiatives, national-level research or arts achievements  

UPCOMING ADMISSIONS-RELATED TIMELINES FOR ALUMNI  
• Mid-June – Virtual Q&A with Admissions leadership for alumni and new admits  
• Early July – Regional send-off receptions hosted by Alumni Chapters  
• Late August – Move-in & Convocation (start of Welcome Week)  
(A finalized public calendar will be shared once posted.)  

ADDITIONAL RESOURCES  
• Internal Admissions Cycle Overview dashboard (Notion) – let me know if you’d like access and I can add you.  
• Aggregate Class Highlights report (Notion) – same as above.  

Both resources contain aggregate data only (no personally identifiable applicant information). Let me know if you need anything else or if Sarah has follow-up questions.

Best regards,  
John

---

Feel free to let me know if you’d like any tweaks!
